                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <title ref="LIT1019Actsof" type="complete" xml:lang="gez">መጽሐፈ፡ ግብረ፡ ልዑካን፡ ዝንቱ፡ ውእቱ፡ ዜና፡
                ሐዋርያት፡ ንጹሓን፡ እምጊዜ፡ ዕርገቱ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዘጸሐፈ፡ ሉቃስ፡ ጠቢብ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡
              ወፈነዎ፡ ኀበ፡ ታኦፊላ፡ ዘጸሐፈ፡ ሎቱ፡ ቀዳሚ፡ ወንግለ።</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                     <note>The chapters are irregularly marked and not numbered.</note>
                     <explicit xml:lang="gez">እስከዝ፡ ነገር፡ አብጽሐ፡ ሉቃስ፡ በዜናሁ። ወእምዝ፡ ተስወረ፡ እምኔሁ፡
              እስመ፡ አንተ፡ ትረክብ፡ በቀዳሚ፡ ፍካሬ፡ መልእክተ፡ ጳውሎስ፡ ዜና፡ ግብረ፡ ጳውሎስ። እስመ፡ ውእቱ፡ ቦአ፡
              ኀበ፡ ኔሮን፡ በቀዳማይ፡ ጊዜ፡ ሞአ፡ ወሖረ፡ በሰላም። ወእምድኅረዝ፡ ነበረ፡ ኑኀ፡ ፪ዓመታተ፡ 
              ወወጽአ። ወእምዝ፡ ተመይጠ፡ ወአጥመቀ፡ አዝማዲሁ፡
              ለኔሮን፡ ወስምዓ፡ ኮነ፡ በአዴሁ፡ በሰይፍ፡ ዕጉሠ።</explicit>
                     <!--  <explicit xml:lang="en">Luke brought his account until here. You will find what is
                missing here at the beginning of the exposition of Paul's epistle, that is the
                <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1016Actsof">Acts of Paul</ref>. He went to 
                <persName ref="PRS7550Nero">Nero</persName>, 
              triumphed and went away in peace. Then he stayed for two years and left. Then he
              returned and baptised <persName ref="PRS7550Nero">Nero</persName>'s parents 
                and patiently became a martyr by his hands, by the
              sword.</explicit>-->
                     <note>The text generally agrees with that of <bibl>
                           <ptr target="bm:Platt1830novum"/>
                        </bibl>,  which represents the revised version.</note>
                  </msItem>
              
